i = 1, if the gene at position i in the list participates in the specified GO term or KEGG pathway and h
i = 0, if the gene at position i in the list does not participate in the specified GO term or KEGG pathway [113, 114]. For each pathway or term, we obtained a profile for r = 30. A value of 1 indicates that all genes in an interval participate in a given GO term or KEGG pathway. We read the resulting profiles along the ordered list as indicative of the level of enrichment with genes of a given GO term or KEGG pathway. Interpretation of transcriptograms is then facilitated by comparing the enrichment profiles from regions with significant difference in their transcriptograms.

